Third-Party Components
======================

Detection & Classification Models
----------------------------------
WatchMyBirds downloads AI models at runtime for object detection and species
classification. These models are NOT part of this project and are licensed
separately by their respective authors. Refer to the upstream model
repositories for applicable license terms before redistribution.


Data Sources
------------
  - Wikipedia — Species descriptions and images are retrieved at runtime.
    Text and media are available under the Creative Commons
    Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International (CC BY-SA 4.0) license.
    See: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

  - Open-Meteo — Weather data is provided by the Open-Meteo API.
    Data is available under the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0
    International (CC BY 4.0) license.
    See: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/


Software & Tools
----------------
  - Label Studio — Annotation tool by HumanSignal, Inc., used under the
    terms of the Label Studio Academic Program.
    See: https://labelstud.io

  - go2rtc — WebRTC/RTSP relay used for low-latency camera streaming.
    Licensed under the MIT License.
    See: https://github.com/AlexxIT/go2rtc